This paper is primarily focused on the optimization of mobile edge caching, which is a key issue in the field of computer networks and communication (cs.NI). The proposed mechanism is based on auction theory, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves the calculation of optimal cache space allocation and user payments, which requires the use of information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of content delivery quality, which is related to the field of signal processing and information theory (cs.SI).
